cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC 

The paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves statistical queries and agnostic learning, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of matrix factorization norms suggests a connection to linear algebra and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and complexity theory (cs.CC) in its characterization of sample complexity.
